---
import Page from '~/layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page
  title="Documentation — DataSUS ETL"
  description="Technical reference: CLI, Python API, architecture, schemas."
  locale="en"
  currentKey="docs"
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-24">
    <p class="stamp text-clinic-red">Documentation</p>
    <h1 class="display-serif mt-3 text-display-lg text-ink">Technical reference.</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-lead text-ink-800 max-w-prose-wide">
      Everything a developer or data engineer needs to automate, embed,
      or extend DataSUS ETL. The desktop app is a convenience — the
      engine is the CLI, the Python API, and the partitioned parquet
      store underneath.
    </p>

    <hr class="hairline mt-10" />

    <nav class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <a href="./cli/" class="group block border border-ink/15 hover:border-clinic-red transition-colors p-6 bg-paper-50">
        <div class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 01</div>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display text-ink group-hover:text-clinic-red transition-colors">CLI reference</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          <code class="font-mono">datasus pipeline</code>,
          <code class="font-mono">update</code>,
          <code class="font-mono">status</code>,
          <code class="font-mono">db</code>,
          <code class="font-mono">ui</code>. Shared flags, exit codes,
          scripting recipes.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./python-api/" class="group block border border-ink/15 hover:border-clinic-red transition-colors p-6 bg-paper-50">
        <div class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 02</div>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display text-ink group-hover:text-clinic-red transition-colors">Python API</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          The same pipeline, imported as a library. Useful when you want
          the ETL inside a larger workflow (Airflow, Prefect,
          notebook-driven analysis).
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./architecture/" class="group block border border-ink/15 hover:border-clinic-red transition-colors p-6 bg-paper-50">
        <div class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 03</div>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display text-ink group-hover:text-clinic-red transition-colors">Architecture</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          How the pieces fit. Path resolution, legacy migration, SPA
          bundling, tkinter-in-subprocess, and the release pipeline.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a href="./schemas/" class="group block border border-ink/15 hover:border-clinic-red transition-colors p-6 bg-paper-50">
        <div class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 04</div>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display text-ink group-hover:text-clinic-red transition-colors">Subsystem schemas</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
          SIHSUS and SIM column lists, types, enrichments. What is
          identical to the DATASUS original, what has been cleaned, and
          where you can read the SQL that did it.
        </p>
      </a>
    </nav>

    <aside class="mt-16 border-l-2 border-clinic-sage pl-6">
      <div class="stamp text-clinic-sage">Maintainer note</div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-600 max-w-prose-wide leading-relaxed">
        The docs below are the user-facing summary. For the canonical
        source of truth on any detail, read the repository — every code
        path referenced here is linked directly to its file and line on
        GitHub.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</Page>
